5, the notations 'R', 'C', and 'M'  denote the operations of rewrite, crossover, and mutate, respectively.Our observations indicate that refraining from employing EoT prompting for problem rewriting results in a discernible decline in model performance across all tasks. This underscores the importance of augmenting the model's comprehension of problems through a more profound engagement, thereby fostering more effective inference. Furthermore,in the course of generating our EoT prompts, the omission of crossover or mutation processes results in a signifi cant performance decrease across all tasks except the SVAMP dataset. Notably, the AQuA dataset exhibits a pronounced performance degradation, emphasizing the indispensability of the crossover and mutation processes in the effective generation of our EoT prompting.
